# Felhaven / Metis secrets — TEMPLATE.
#
# This file is committed and holds NO real secrets. Copy it to `.env` in the
# same directory and fill in your keys there (`.env` is gitignored):
#
#     copy .env.example .env        (Windows)
#     cp   .env.example .env        (macOS / Linux)
#
# Format: one KEY=value per line. '#' starts a comment. A real OS environment
# variable (e.g. set via `setx`) takes precedence over anything in `.env`.
#
# NOTE: API keys consumed by the toolbox's tools (Finnhub, Brave, ...) live in
# the Cerberus Vault now, not here — seed them with:
#     python cerberus.py set <PIN> <name> <value>
# .env is still available for anything that hasn't been migrated to the Vault.
